-- Piaggio Targets $381 Million Ebitda in 2013 on Asia Sales, Production Gain
-- B y   T o m m a s o   E b h a r d t
-- 2010-09-23T06:57:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-23/piaggio-targeting-higher-earnings-through-2013-by-boosting-asian-sales.html
Piaggio & C. SpA, the Italian maker
of Vespa scooters, targets earnings before interest, tax,
depreciation and amortization of 285 million euros and 1.9
billion euros revenue in 2013, according to a statement
distributed by the Italian exchange.  The Italian company expects to increase its sales in Asia
and to build new plants in India and Vietnam.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tommaso Ebhardt at 
 tebhardt@bloomberg.net  